column1: This is a mapping from google mymaps icons to galileo. The color codes for google maps aren't 100% direct translations, but I tried to match them.

column7: I think this is supposed to be a bike trail but that's not in google maps
google maps has dice, this has cards. shrug!

the *first* thing that came to mind was spectrum analyzer. But that's not correct, of course. But the next thing was "stock market or something" and google has something similar with financial services, so I'll match it to that.
... not really sure. google maps has a "missing person" but I doubt this is that.
not a super direct mapping here. I think this is "office". could be apartment. There's "city" and "downtown" in google maps. downtown seemed closer?
not really certain on this. It's red, so it leads me to believe something something emergency. but there's veterinarian below. Vet -> animal services. This -> animal shelter. Sure.

in google maps there's what I would think of for pharmacy, and this is "pharmacy (europe)" ... so despite my american centricness, I stayed true to the app :) perhaps I'll accept both when converting from google maps to galileo

to me this says "shopping basket". the cart is like a full on supermarket, this is more like a smaller grocery store? I dunno. Especially because the purple ones seem to be shopping / retail oriented.
isn't really a toy store in google maps, but robots are toys right
honestly I had no idea, but I saw the google maps icon and went with it. it fits with the color category
